column5: https://www.canadafishingguide.net/oh-betty-running-down-the-little-current-from-percy/
Very nice man!
Nice write up Chris. Like that shirt . Trade ya for a Sens jersey.
sweet report, warmer days warmer days will soon be here
Great write up. I especially found the rock pictures very interesting, so different. Amazing fishing by the looks of your haul. That would be a dream trip for me..... Thanks for sharing.
What a report! A pleasure to read it.
awesome TR and photos, thanks Chris !
One Hell of a report.....enough said !
nice read got me itchin for Nipigon pike in a month!
Cheaper than Howard's on Stinger? Is that why you didn't go back there??  BTW---How's your friend, the Borgerman?
Percy is a helluva good bang for the buck as far as a Fly in goes in that area and I'm not sure what stingers rates are currently because Howard no longer owns it Pennocks bought it two years ago.
Great write up and amazing catch. I'd love to do a fly in but I fear being out of range of a hospital. I never know when an infection of some kind will flare up.

Borgerman is good. He's got a head start, but if I paddle fast I'm gonna catch up and see him tomorrow. Drive in, but I'd go back to Stinger in a heartbeat. I loved it. I just wish the camp would have ended up in different hands, Jason's hands to be specific, lol.
Some guy left a floating marker out there.............?

Have heard that buzz before in the woods... INTENSE buzz that builds at dark, stays a short while and almost suddenly stops. You write them better than anyone really. And a great mix of photos. Have had this one up on the screen a couple days knowing not to miss it. Glad that didn't happen. Enjoy the next stop bud!
Wow, what a great post/report. I’d love to check this place out!
Awesome report Chris. Beauty spot.
Nice write up. I am missing my annual trip this year so these stories will have to keep my satisfied!
Missing your annual trip? That's just wrong. Hope it's not health related and just a hard schedule. If you find time this summer give me a shout may be I can help you out
Nice write-up and a great read! Love giant pike and you guys got some beauties! Those rocks were pretty intriguing as well!
